bled` to prevent interaction."},"806":{"id":"/docs/components/select-23","page_id":"/docs/components/select","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/select#form","content":"Set `name` to submit the value with a native `<form>`. Multiple-mode values submit as repeated entries with the same `name`."},"807":{"id":"/docs/components/tag","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"page","content":"Tag","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag"},"808":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-0","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag","content":"Non-interactive labels that highlight statuses and categories."},"809":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-1","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#installation","content":"Installation"},"810":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-2","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#props","content":"Props"},"811":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-3","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#examples","content":"Examples"},"812":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-4","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#basic","content":"Basic"},"813":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-5","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#emphasis","content":"Emphasis"},"814":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-6","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#sizes","content":"Sizes"},"815":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-7","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#inline","content":"Inline"},"816":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-8","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#high-contrast","content":"High Contrast"},"817":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-9","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#with-icon","content":"With Icon"},"818":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-10","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator","content":"Indicator"},"819":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-11","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#accessibility","content":"Accessibility"},"820":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-12","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#screen-readers","content":"Screen readers"},"821":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-13","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#decorative-icons","content":"Decorative icons"},"822":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-14","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator-dot","content":"Indicator dot"},"823":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-15","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Best Practices"},"824":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-16","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"When to Use"},"825":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-17","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"When Not to Use"},"826":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-18","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#basic","content":"A minimal tag with the default emphasis and size."},"827":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-19","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#emphasis","content":"Nine emphasis options are available. Choose the one that fits the visual tone of your context."},"828":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-20","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#sizes","content":"Choose a size that fits the surrounding content. Smaller tags work well in compact layouts like tables; larger tags suit headings or hero sections."},"829":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-21","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#inline","content":"Use `design=\"inline\"` to embed a tag within a sentence. The background and border are removed so the tag blends into the text flow."},"830":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-22","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#high-contrast","content":"A bolder color treatment for when tags need to stand out more — for example, on colored backgrounds."},"831":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-23","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#with-icon","content":"Icons reinforce the tag's meaning at a glance. Add an `Icon` as a child — it inherits the tag's color and scales with its size."},"832":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-24","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator","content":"A minimal style that pairs a small colored dot with a neutral background. Well suited for dense layouts like tables or dashboards where multiple tags in close proximity would otherwise compete for attention."},"833":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-25","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#screen-readers","content":"Tags are `<span>` elements with no special ARIA role. Screen readers announce the tag's text as part of normal page content — no extra markup is needed."},"834":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-26","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#decorative-icons","content":"Icons passed as children must include `aria-hidden=\"true\"` so they are skipped by screen readers. The text label is the sole carrier of meaning."},"835":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-27","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#indicator-dot","content":"The colored dot is decorative and invisible to screen readers. The text label must convey the status on its own — never rely on the dot alone to communicate meaning."},"836":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-28","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Use the indicator style in dense layouts like tables and dashboards. Use the filled style when the tag is a prominent, standalone element on a card or hero section."},"837":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-29","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Default to the small size in compact layouts like tables and lists. Use medium or large only when the tag needs to stand out as a primary piece of information."},"838":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-30","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Use the inline design only within running prose. In grouped or standalone contexts, the filled style provides better visual separation."},"839":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-31","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#best-practices","content":"Do not stack multiple tags of different emphasis on the same item. Choose the most important one — too many competing labels lose their meaning."},"840":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-32","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Showing the status of an item on a card, table row, or list entry (e.g. \"Active\", \"Expired\", \"Pending\")"},"841":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-33","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Categorizing or grouping content so users can scan and filter quickly (e.g. \"New\", \"Sale\", \"Beta\")"},"842":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-34","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Surfacing metadata about an item (e.g. \"Pro\", \"Free trial\", \"Internal\")"},"843":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-35","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-to-use","content":"Communicating priority or category in project management and collaboration tools (e.g. \"High priority\", \"In review\")"},"844":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-36","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"If users need to click or dismiss it — use a **Button** instead."},"845":{"id":"/docs/components/tag-37","page_id":"/docs/components/tag","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/tag#when-not-to-use","content":"If the label is part of a sentence with no visual distinction — just use text."},"846":{"id":"/docs/components/text","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"page","content":"Text","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text"},"847":{"id":"/docs/components/text-0","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text","content":"Text component for displaying and formatting text content with alignment and truncation options"},"848":{"id":"/docs/components/text-1","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#installation","content":"Installation"},"849":{"id":"/docs/components/text-2","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#props","content":"Props"},"850":{"id":"/docs/components/text-3","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#examples","content":"Examples"},"851":{"id":"/docs/components/text-4","page_id":"/docs/components/text","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text#as","content":"As"},"852":{"id":"/docs/components/text-5"