:[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"Setting the `wrap` prop allows you to change the wrapping of the text. The values can be `wrap`, `nowrap`, `balance`, `pretty`, or `stable`."},"861":{"id":"/docs/components/text-14","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`wrap` is the setting that is most commonly used. For most elements you will not to explicitly set this."},"862":{"id":"/docs/components/text-15","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`nowrap` should be avoided except in cases where it is important to prevent the text from wrapping."},"863":{"id":"/docs/components/text-16","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`balance` is most commonly used for headlines, titles, and labels."},"864":{"id":"/docs/components/text-17","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`pretty` is most commonly used for body text."},"865":{"id":"/docs/components/text-18","page_id":"/docs/components/text","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text#wrap","content":"`stable` is commonly used for editable text, such as textareas."},"866":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","type":"page","content":"TextField","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/text-field"},"867":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-0","page_id":"/docs/components/text-field","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/text-field","content":"TextField is a single-line or multiline text input with optional label, description, and error message. Use it in forms for short answers (email, search, name) or longer content (comments). It supports optional leading and trailing text adornments (e.g. currency or units)."},"868":{"id":"/docs/components/text-field-1","page_id":